Texture Takeaways:

✅ Low & Slow - it’s easy to “Break” a Curl Pattern so use low volumes of peroxide, gentle lightener types, & bond builders 

Example: @oligopro Lightening Cream (the *Best* Oil Based Lightener) & @olaplex

✅ Chunky Pick-Ups - skinny highlights disappear when Curl Expands so try Zigzag Teasie-Lights 

Technique Combo: 

#GeodesicFoilayage + 
#HairlineShuffle + 
#LockStitchFoilayage

✅ Carve and Slice - cut across the hair at angle 📐 (never shave on top of the cuticle with a blade parallel to the hair) and slice internal weight to avoid the “Pyramid Look” 

* Also, disconnected Layers creates shorter pieces underneath that internally push up long layers for Crown Volume without too short of layers at the Top 🔝

✅ Treatment 🎁 @k18hair 💪

💦 Gloss Formula:

@oligopro Calura Gloss 
Roots 7N & 7AI 
Mids-Ends 9GV & 10NB

Tool ⚒️ @ashleenormanhair 6.75 Shears ✂️

Client: “I need a Haircut BUT - I Don’t want to lose any length, I Don’t want Bangs, All the Layers need to go back into a Ponytail, I Want to be able to part it anywhere, and I Want Movement & Shape” 

Hairstylist: 🤔🤨😳....💡🤯🤓

1. “M” Frame - “V” + Side Bits = A center point of weight that can swing to either side part or even from the middle with connected side layers

2. “V” Layer in Top Horseshoe (Cutting on the “Bias”) - crisscrossing diagonal sections to once again create a center point of weight that can swing like a pendulum 

3. Connect sides to Faceframe for Round length line 

4. Concave Layers Undercut below Top Horseshoe - Internal weight removal 

*Disconnected Layers swing separately from each other to maximize movement in the back without creating short layers at the top crown 👸

Step 2: Section the Front from the back from where the Top of Head rounds forward to the front of the Ears 

Step 3: Pre-Dry focusing on the Root Direction - flat wrap the roots opposite to natural fall to create Volume using the @dysonhairpro Super Sonic Pro

Step 4: Section in 3 large Cirlces - starting in the Hairline front to back

Step 5: Flat Brush “C” Shapes into the Hair by over-directing the hair forward and then back using a @behairfulbrush 

Notes 📝 

* direct the nozzle of the blow dryer down the cuticle layer not straight at the hair using the face of the boar hair brush to smooth and create shine ✨ 

* Never touch the nozzle to the brush - if the natural boar hair bristles of the brush become burnt 🥵 then what do you think is happening to the clients hair? 

Step 6: Spray ANH “Roll in the Hay” Texture Spray thoroughly section by section directed at the roots to soak up oils and add volume 

Step 7: Scrunch in ANH “Oh Behave Cream” at the Mids-ends to add separations and definition

How to Balayage Redhead 👩‍🦰 

My model at my recent #TripleThreatFoilayage class was a redhead with a level 6 permanent tint. 

I wanted to add dimension without taking her too blonde for her completion. I wanted the look of open air painting but needed foils to lift through the tint. 

After shaping up her Haircut 💇‍♀️ 
I taught my signature technique of breaking down brick 🧱 layered Balayage Triangles 🔼 into 3 foils each ( Triple Threat 😘 ) and added auburn lowlights in-between. 

Then I ColorMelted with an Auburn Shadow Root and Strawberry 🍓 Blonde 👱‍♀️ Gloss 

Formulas:

Lightener @oligopro Cool Blonde 👱‍♀️ & @olaplex 💦 

Lowlights @schwarzkopfusa TBH 5-47 & 8-47 1:1 13vol

ColorMelt @schwarzkopfusa TBH

Root 5-47 + 6-06 + 6-19  1:1:1 6vol and Tone Softener 

Hairline- Mids-Ends 10-56 + 9-47
1:1:1 13vol and Tone Softener 

Treatment @k18hair

What’s the difference between Building a Brand and Building a Legacy?

To me- building a brand is about building Awareness of a Product or Service - building a Legacy is about leaving a lasting Impact 💥 

Branding is how the market Perceives the Value of your offerings. 

Legacy is how people are Impacted by your Brand’s Services/ Products.

It’s possible to have a Strong Brand and leave a Negative Impact but it is Not possible to have a Strong Legacy with a Negative Brand. 

👉👉Swipe 👉 👉

@janet.studiocultive ‘s experience with my education Brand affirms my Purpose and Mission. We meet 6 years ago when she attended my class for the first time. Every year since she either attended or helped facilitate my education in the Coeur d’Alene, Idaho. This year was extra special because she Hosted at her very own brand new salon @studiocultive and modeled for me! 

These Relationships with my colleagues that I have all over the World are proof of God’s Faithfulness - Not to Glorify myself but to make a lasting positive Impact 💥

Shout out to my @anh_crew Team Member @hair.juancarlos for Hair and Photo Credit 💪🙌💕

node.text:
Happiest 6th Birthday 🥳 to my first born, my Beautiful Boy #mrcameronleenorman 

Cameron, you completely Rocked my World the day I found out I was pregnant. You changed me from a selfish girl into a woman. You put everything else into perspective and taught me love I never knew existed. The day you were born I could m not stop kissing your sweet little face. Snuggling you, smelling you, nursing you was the most incredible experience. I took you everywhere with me for the first 2 years of your life as I became a traveling educator when I was only 6 weeks pregnant with you. We traveled with Grandma and you to saw, tasted, and experienced more places in the first few years of your life than many people do in their lifetime. Since we were so close, of course things got a little competitive when baby sister came along. But you eventually got over your jealousy and now you two can be the best playmates. You are Charming and Brilliant. It’s really not fair that you got both your parents gifts, Dadda’s Intelligence and Momma’s Charisma. I fear what trouble those big blue eyes will get you in and will be there to do what I can to protect you from heartbreak (but also from breaking hearts 😅😬). Although you are in a prestigious private school, they still can’t keep you challenged in Math and we have to take you to Tutoring just so you don’t get bored at school even though you are only in Kindergarten. Apparently you are a Romantic as you are already in Love “so much that it hurts”. I love that you are still open to me and tell me things when it’s just the two of us doing your bedtime reading. I hope we stay close over the years. I know we’ll have many fights as you grow into a Man. I just hope one day I’ll get to hold your son or daughter and fall in love all over again. I hope I’m a good enough parent, that you trust me to be involved in your future family the same way your Grandparents are all over you ‘like white in rice’. Love you Forever my Gorgeous Son 💕

Texture Takeaways:

✅ Low & Slow - it’s easy to “Break” a Curl Pattern so use low volumes of peroxide, gentle lightener types, & bond builders 

Example: @oligopro Lightening Cream (the *Best* Oil Based Lightener) & @olaplex

✅ Chunky Pick-Ups - skinny highlights disappear when Curl Expands so try Zigzag Teasie-Lights

#GeodesicFoilayage +
